   {:e #blake3 "a4adc8f5bca2df2ebd5e629f3e316654399f0bdf4bb4c024e613d3aa4d1d76a9" :a :harvest/accomplishments :v "Session entity: :task/t-52a64fdf; Session entity: :task/t-7b63c9c9; Session entity: :task/t-22ab67bc; Session entity: :task/t-19d93e09; AUDIT DEFECTS 011, 012, 014 (STYLE): Three style issues. (011) E2E test 9 in e2e_concept_crystallization.sh:119 assertion is too weak — matches 'connected' from keyword connections, not CCE concept system. Test passes even when concept assignment fails. FIX: split into two assertions; mark concept assertion as expected-fail until SEMANTIC-EMBED ships. (012) Test centroid_of_one_is_itself in embedding.rs:636 actually tests serialization roundtrip, not centroid computation. Misleading name. FIX: rename to embedding_roundtrip_preserves_values. (014) EmbeddingError in embedding.rs:34 doesn't implement std::error::Error, preventing use with Box<dyn Error>. FIX: add impl std::error::Error for EmbeddingError {}. All independent, no dependencies.; Session entity: :task/t-07936f49; Session entity: :task/t-906a704a; Session entity: :session/s-1774433530; Session entity: :task/t-265b24c8; Session entity: :recon/trace-14a7d29a47372d9e; Session entity: :task/t-7a052c34; AUDIT DEFECT-006 (MAJOR): CCE transaction write error silently discarded. observe.rs:601 uses 'let _ = live.write_tx(&cce_tx)' — if disk is full or permissions fail, the observation appears to succeed but embedding, concept assignment, and entity links are silently lost. The main observation datoms (body, confidence, category) are written earlier with error propagation, but the CCE follow-up transaction is fire-and-forget. FIX: Replace 'let _ = live.write_tx(&cce_tx)' with 'live.write_tx(&cce_tx)?'. One-character change. TEST: Error path testing requires filesystem mocking (not practical for unit tests). The happy path is covered by existing tests. INTERACTION: Independent of other defects.; Session entity: :task/t-dd839eea; AUDIT DEFECT-004 (MAJOR, downgraded from CRITICAL): cosine_similarity dimension mismatch uses debug_assert only — disabled in release. embedding.rs:282. If caller passes vectors of different lengths, zip silently truncates and produces wrong similarity. HOWEVER: all internal call sites check dimensions first (find_nearest_concept line 117 checks concept_emb.len() == embedding.len()). Risk is only for external callers of the public function. FIX: Keep debug_assert for performance. Document the precondition clearly. Consider adding a #[cfg(debug_assertions)] runtime check. For a cleanroom fix: return 0.0 on mismatch with an eprintln diagnostic, rather than silently computing wrong answer. INTERACTION: This is orthogonal to other defects. No dependencies.; Session entity: :task/t-4d58a2c3; Session entity: :task/t-9c0b0ead; AUDIT DEFECT-002 (CRITICAL): unwrap() in production code at concept.rs:119. find_nearest_concept uses 'if best.is_none() || sim > best.unwrap().1' — the unwrap is unreachable due to short-circuit evaluation, but fragile under refactoring. Any future edit adding an OR condition could trigger a panic. Violates INV-EMBEDDING-003 (no panics on invalid input). FIX: Replace with 'if best.map_or(true, |(_, s)| sim > s)'. Semantically identical, panic-proof. No new tests needed — existing tests cover both None and Some paths. Zero regression risk.; AUDIT DEFECT-007 (MAJOR): concept_inventory makes TWO full datom scans. concept.rs:260-313 first scans for :concept/name to build entity set, then rescans ALL datoms to fill remaining attributes. At 88K datoms this doubles scan cost for a function called on every braid status. FIX: Single-pass collection — check all concept-related attributes in one loop body. If entity is already in the map, update it. If d.attribute is :concept/name, insert-or-update. If d.attribute is any other concept attr and entity is in map, update. This halves the iterations. INTERACTION: Related to DEFECT-015 (format_concept_status O(D*C^2)) which calls concept_inventory. Fixing both together gives best speedup.; Session entity: :task/t-80bb132a; Session entity: :task/t-567d61da; AUDIT DEFECT-005 (MAJOR): find_nearest_concept sees stale concept embeddings. concept.rs:107-127 scans ALL datoms including retracted ones. If a concept embedding is updated (new Assert without Retract of old), both old and new assertion datoms exist. The function iterates in datom order and takes the LAST match per entity (due to overwriting best), but this depends on insertion order being chronological — which is true for BTreeSet<Datom> ordered by EAVT, but fragile. More importantly: if EMBED-CONSISTENCY re-embeds innate concepts, the old hash embeddings and new model embeddings both exist as Assert datoms for the same entity+attribute. The function would compare against whichever the iterator yields last. FIX: Collect latest embedding per entity into a BTreeMap, then search that map. This also incorporates the DEFECT-002 fix (map_or pattern). TEST: Assert two embeddings for same concept entity, verify find_nearest_concept uses the latest. DEPENDS-ON: DEFECT-002 fix (same function).; Session entity: :task/t-19b0b27f; Session entity: :task/t-64e6797a\nAUDIT DEFECTS 008, 009, 010, 013 (MINOR): Four minor code quality issues. (008) generate_concept_name at concept.rs:892-900 calls connections::tokenize twice per document — once for TF, once for DF. FIX: compute unique from words. (009) MIN_MATCH_LEN=5 too low for common English words like 'error', 'state', 'model', 'value', 'query' that appear as package name segments. FIX: raise to 7 or add stopword list. Severity uncertain — depends on project naming. (010) TF-IDF sort uses partial_cmp with unwrap_or at concept.rs:913. FIX: use f64::total_cmp(). (013) Variance stored as Value::Bytes (raw f64 LE) while total_weight uses Value::Double. Inconsistent — both are floating point. FIX: use Value::Double for variance too. None of these have dependencies on other defects.; AUDIT DEFECT-015 (MAJOR): format_concept_status has O(D*C^2) complexity. concept.rs:734-741 calls is_innate() for each concept — is_innate does a full datom scan (88K). With 25 concepts this is 25*88K = 2.2M iterations just for fade check. Then the filter at line 741 calls is_innate AGAIN for the same concepts. FIX: Collect innate entity IDs in a HashSet from a single scan pass, then use set membership. Combine with DEFECT-007 fix (single-pass concept_inventory could also collect innate flags). TEST: Performance test with synthetic store of 100K datoms and 20 concepts — format_concept_status should complete in < 10ms. INTERACTION: Blocks on same code region as DEFECT-007.; AUDIT DEFECT-003 (CRITICAL): Agglomerative clustering centroids NOT L2-normalized after merge. concept.rs lines 202-204 compute weighted-average centroid but never call l2_normalize. Consequence: stored concept centroids (NewConcept.centroid, written to :concept/embedding) violate INV-EMBEDDING-002 (normalized vectors). Cosine similarity still works (handles unnormalized vectors), but surprise calculations on stored centroids diverge from what normalized centroids would produce. The centroid shrinks toward zero as clusters grow, making surprise values systematically wrong for large concepts. FIX: Add l2_normalize(&mut centroids[best_i]) after line 205 in crystallize_concepts. Requires making l2_normalize pub(crate) or adding a public normalize wrapper. TEST: Verify each NewConcept.centroid from crystallize_concepts has L2 norm within 1e-5 of 1.0. REGRESSION: Changes centroid values slightly. Normalized centroids are more correct and match what embed() functions produce.; Session entity: :task/t-926e3284" :op :assert}
